# Royal — Product Requirements Document

Last updated: 2026-04-06

---

## What Royal is

Royal is a wellness tracking and social platform — Strava, but for workouts and wellness. Users log and track their fitness and wellness life in detail, share it with a community, and earn royalties when others use their product referral links.

The priority order matters: logging and tracking is the core product. Social sharing is the layer on top. The royalties/catalog feature is a tasteful addition that rewards people for the recommendations they'd be making anyway.

Available on iOS. App Store: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/royal-fitness-wellness/id6759988491

---

## The problem Royal solves

Strava owns the running and cycling space because it made activity tracking social without making it performative. Nothing does that for the broader world of fitness and wellness — gym workouts, nutrition, recovery, sleep, sauna, skincare, supplements.

Royal fills that gap. It also adds something Strava doesn't have: a tasteful way to earn from the products and places you already recommend to people.

---

## Target user

**Primary**: Gen Z and Millennial (roughly 20–35), health-conscious, active lifestyle. Not necessarily an influencer or content creator — just someone who genuinely cares about how they live and wants a place to track and share it.

**Secondary**: Nano-influencers and wellness creators (under 5K followers) who want a platform built around their actual lifestyle rather than content performance metrics.

**Who Royal is not for**: People chasing follower counts, people who want a calorie-counting app, people looking for a get-rich-quick affiliate scheme.

